text: Hey Eugene how's it going what brings you in today
Hey. I'm just feeling worn out all the time. My girlfriend convinced me to get checked out because of some strange things happening with my body.
why don't you tell me about those strange things
Well, my legs swell up pretty bad, and I'm tired all the time. I also feel like throwing up most days. That's about all I've noticed.
have you recently had any symptoms such as fever or stomach pain or runny nose
I haven't had a fever or a runny nose. My stomach's been off lately, though â€” feels like throwing up most days.
when did these symptoms start
They started getting worse after I stopped working. It's been a few months now.
when did they when did they first start
I guess they first started a few months back, before I stopped working.
again why did you stop working
I stopped working because I was too weak and tired to keep up with my plumbing jobs.
do you have any other health conditions
I've had high blood pressure since my thirties.
what is it normal blood pressure for you
My blood pressure's usually on the high side, even with medication. Can't say the exact numbers off the top of my head.
what medications do you take
I have a whole bunch of medicines I'm on that I can't pronounce. My girlfriend makes me keep a list in my wallet.
can I see the list
Sure, the list includes furosemide, nifedipine, potassium chloride, clonidine patch, clopidogrel, atenolol, iron, and aspirin.
does anything make your symptmoms better or worse?
Resting seems to help a bit, but not much else makes a difference. Moving around too much definitely makes things worse, especially with the swelling and fatigue.
have you had any changes in your urination
Yeah, I pee less than I used to. Sometimes it's dark, but I figured I just wasn't drinking enough.
where are you currently being treated for anything
I've been in and out of the doctor's office lately, and sometimes back in the hospital for more tests.
do you have any heart issues
I haven't been diagnosed with any heart issues, but I sometimes wonder if my heart's giving out with all these symptoms. My blood pressure's been high for years, though.
can you list every single symptom you have please

I feel worn out all the time, my legs swell up, I feel like throwing up most days, and there's this metallic taste in my mouth. I also smell ammonia a lot, my girlfriend says my breath smells fishy, and I wake up with a white powder on my skin. My legs twitch at night, and I get confused sometimes. That's about all I can say on that.
do you have any family history
Yeah, my dad had high blood pressure and diabetes, and I think he had kidney disease too. He died young, at 45. My mom had breast cancer and passed away at 60.
do you smoke
No, I don't smoke.
do you have any joint or bone pain
Yeah, I've got this deep ache in my bones, like I've been hauling pipe all day.
have you ever had any surgeries
No, I haven't had any surgeries.
have you had any injuries or trauma
No significant injuries or trauma that I can think of.
any recent hospitalizations
I've been in the hospital a few times recently for tests and lung congestion.
what test
I don't really know all the specifics, but they've been running various tests to figure out what's going on with my symptoms. You'd have to ask the doctors for details.
do you have any allergies
None that I know of.
how are you finances
Things are a bit tight since I'm not working right now, but we're managing.
do you have insurance
Yeah, I've got insurance.
what kind
I'm not sure of the specifics, but I have some coverage through my work. You'd have to ask the doctors for details.
wheres your girlfriend
She's at home right now. She's been really supportive through all this.
